trans-unit.source: Represents an easing function that creates an animation that resembles a spring oscillating back and forth until it comes to rest.
trans-unit.target: Representerer en easing funksjon som oppretter en animasjon som ligner en vår oscillating frem og tilbake til det kommer til resten.

trans-unit.source: You can control when in the "spring" behavior occurs in an animation by specifying the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A> property value.
trans-unit.target: Du kan kontrollere når i "vår" skjer i en animasjon ved å angi den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>egenskapsverdi.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>

trans-unit.source: The following graph demonstrates the different values of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>, where *f*(*t*) represents the animation progress and *t* represents time.
trans-unit.target: Følgende diagrammet viser ulike verdier for <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>, der *f*(*t*) representerer animasjonen fremdriften og *t* representerer klokkeslett.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>

trans-unit.source: ![ElasticEase with graphs of different easingmodes.](~/add/media/elasticease-graph.png "ElasticEase with graphs of different easingmodes.")
trans-unit.target: ![ElasticEase med diagrammer med ulike easingmodes. ] (~/add/media/elasticease-graph.png "ElasticEase med diagrammer med ulike easingmodes.")

trans-unit.source: You can specify how many times the animation oscillates back and forth using the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase.Oscillations%2A> property and how tight the springiness of the oscillations are using the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase.Springiness%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Du kan angi hvor mange ganger animasjonen oscillates frem og tilbake med den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase.Oscillations%2A>egenskapen og hvordan tett springiness av oscillations bruker den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase.Springiness%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase.Springiness%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase.Oscillations%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Because this animation causes values to oscillate back and forth, the animation might interpolate into negative numbers unexpectedly.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Fordi denne animasjonen fører til at verdier oscillate frem og tilbake, animasjonen kan uventet interpolere til negative tall.

trans-unit.source: This can cause errors when animating properties that do not allow negative numbers.
trans-unit.target: Dette kan føre til feil når animere egenskaper som ikke tillater negative tall.

trans-unit.source: For example, if you apply this animation to the <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A> of an object (e.g. from 0 to 200 with an <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A> of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>), the animation will attempt to interpolate through negative numbers for <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A> which will throw an error.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du bruker denne animasjon til for eksempel den <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A>objektets (eksempel fra 0 til 200 med en <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>av <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>), animasjonen vil prøve å interpolere via negative tall for <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A>som vil throw en feil.</xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A> </xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A>

trans-unit.source: There are several other easing functions besides ElasticEase which you can explore using the following Silverlight sample.
trans-unit.target: Det er flere easing funksjoner i tillegg til ElasticEase som du kan utforske ved å bruke følgende Silverlight-utvalg.

trans-unit.source: [Run this sample](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=139798&sref=easing_functions_gallery) In addition to using the easing functions included in the run-time, you can create your own custom easing functions by inheriting from <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase>.
trans-unit.target: [Kjør dette eksemplet](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=139798&sref=easing_functions_gallery) i tillegg til ved hjelp av de easing funksjonene som er inkludert i kjøretid, kan du opprette egendefinerte easing funksjoner ved arving fra <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Initialiserer en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.ElasticEase"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: Creates a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Freezable"></xref> derived class.
trans-unit.target: Oppretter en ny forekomst av den <xref href="System.Windows.Freezable"> </xref> avledet klasse.

trans-unit.source: When creating a derived class, you must override this method.
trans-unit.target: Når du oppretter en avledet klasse, må du overstyre denne metoden.

trans-unit.source: Animation classes inherit indirectly from <xref:System.Windows.Freezable>.
trans-unit.target: Animasjon-klasser arve indirekte fra <xref:System.Windows.Freezable>.</xref:System.Windows.Freezable>

trans-unit.source: Because of this, you need to override the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BackEase.CreateInstanceCore%2A> method to construct a custom animation object.
trans-unit.target: Du vil overstyre derfor den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BackEase.CreateInstanceCore%2A>metode for å lage et egendefinert animasjon-objekt.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BackEase.CreateInstanceCore%2A>

trans-unit.source: The new instance.
trans-unit.target: Den nye forekomsten.

trans-unit.source: Provides the logic portion of the easing function that you can override to produce the <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode"></xref> mode of the custom easing function.
trans-unit.target: Gir logic-delen av funksjonen easing som du kan overstyre for å produsere det <xref href="System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode"> </xref> modus for den egendefinerte easing funksjonen.

trans-unit.source: This method transforms normalized time to control the pace of an animation for the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> case of <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden overfører normalisert tid å kontroll over en animasjon for <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>tilfellet for <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A>.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.EasingMode%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>

trans-unit.source: You only have to specify your easing function for the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> case because the implementation of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.Ease%2A> method transforms `normalizedTime` for the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> and <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> cases.
trans-unit.target: Du trenger bare å angi den easing funksjonen for det <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>tilfelle fordi implementeringen av den <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.Ease%2A>metoden transformeringer `normalizedTime` for det <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>og <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>tilfeller.</xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingFunctionBase.Ease%2A> </xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.EasingMode>

trans-unit.source: Normalized time (progress) of the animation.
trans-unit.target: Normalisert klokkeslettet (pågår) animasjonen.

trans-unit.source: A double that represents the transformed progress.
trans-unit.target: En dobbeltverdi som representerer transformert fremdriften.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the stiffness of the spring.
trans-unit.target: Henter eller angir stiffness for vår.

trans-unit.source: The smaller the Springiness value is, the stiffer the spring and the faster the elasticity decreases in intensity over each oscillation.
trans-unit.target: Mindre Springiness-verdien er, jo stiffer vår og raskere fleksibilitet reduserer i intensiteten over hver oscillation.
